{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":833,"text":"So I'd like to tell you a story\nabout climate and change,"},{"time":4680,"text":"but it's really a story about people\nand not polar bears."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8640,"text":"So this is our house\nthat we lived in in the mid-2000s."},{"time":12200,"text":"I was the chief operating officer\nfor the Navy's weather and ocean service."},{"time":17000,"text":"It happened to be down at a place\ncalled Stennis Space Center"},{"time":19920,"text":"right on the Gulf Coast,"},{"time":21200,"text":"so we lived in a little town\ncalled Waveland, Mississippi,"},{"time":23939,"text":"nice modest house, and as you can see,\nit's up against a storm surge."},{"time":27480,"text":"Now, if you ever wonder"},{"time":30160,"text":"what a 30-foot or nine-meter\nstorm surge does"},{"time":33640,"text":"coming up your street,"},{"time":35720,"text":"let me show you."},{"time":37360,"text":"Same house."},{"time":38720,"text":"That's me, kind of wondering what's next."},{"time":42280,"text":"But when we say we lost our house --\nthis is, like, right after Katrina --"},{"time":45800,"text":"so the house is either all the way\nup there in the railway tracks,"},{"time":49640,"text":"or it's somewhere down there\nin the Gulf of Mexico,"},{"time":52480,"text":"and to this day,\nwe really, we lost our house."},{"time":54680,"text":"We don't know where it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57240,"text":"You know, it's gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59120,"text":"So I don't show this for pity,"},{"time":64040,"text":"because in many ways, we were\nthe luckiest people on the Gulf Coast."},{"time":68480,"text":"One of the things is, we had insurance,"},{"time":71360,"text":"and that idea of insurance\nis probably pretty important there."},{"time":75800,"text":"But does this scale up,\nyou know, what happened here?"},{"time":78760,"text":"And I think it kind of does,\nbecause as you've heard,"},{"time":82040,"text":"as the sea levels come up,"},{"time":83760,"text":"it takes weaker and weaker storms\nto do something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87680,"text":"So let's just step back for a second\nand kind of look at this."},{"time":91600,"text":"And, you know,\nclimate's really complicated,"},{"time":94200,"text":"a lot of moving parts in this,"},{"time":97000,"text":"but I kind of put it about\nit's all about the water."},{"time":99920,"text":"See, see those three blue dots\nthere down on the lower part?"},{"time":103320,"text":"The one you can easily see,\nthat's all the water in the world."},{"time":106640,"text":"Those two smaller dots,\nthose are the fresh water."},{"time":110120,"text":"And it turns out\nthat as the climate changes,"},{"time":113480,"text":"the distribution of that water\nis changing very fundamentally."},{"time":117000,"text":"So now we have too much, too little,\nwrong place, wrong time."},{"time":120760,"text":"It's salty where it should be fresh;\nit's liquid where it should be frozen;"},{"time":125360,"text":"it's wet where it should be dry;"},{"time":126960,"text":"and in fact, the very chemistry\nof the ocean itself is changing."},{"time":130759,"text":"And what that does\nfrom a security or a military part"},{"time":135720,"text":"is it does three things:"},{"time":138000,"text":"it changes the very operating\nenvironment that we're working in,"},{"time":141600,"text":"it threatens our bases,"},{"time":143200,"text":"and then it has geostrategic risks,\nwhich sounds kind of fancy"},{"time":146720,"text":"and I'll explain what I mean\nby that in a second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"So let's go to just\na couple examples here."},{"time":153520,"text":"And we'll start off with what we all know"},{"time":155760,"text":"is of course a political\nand humanitarian catastrophe"},{"time":158960,"text":"that is Syria."},{"time":160400,"text":"And it turns out that climate\nwas one of the causes"},{"time":164840,"text":"in a long chain of events."},{"time":167560,"text":"It actually started back in the 1970s."},{"time":170360,"text":"When Assad took control over Syria,"},{"time":173240,"text":"he decided he wanted to be self-sufficient\nin things like wheat and barley."},{"time":178400,"text":"Now, you would like to think"},{"time":180080,"text":"that there was somebody\nin Assad's office that said,"},{"time":182560,"text":"\"Hey boss, you know,\nwe're in the eastern Mediterranean,"},{"time":185680,"text":"kind of dry here,\nmaybe not the best idea.\""},{"time":189160,"text":"But I think what happened was,"},{"time":190640,"text":"\"Boss, you are a smart, powerful\nand handsome man. We'll get right on it.\""},{"time":194760,"text":"And they did."},{"time":196000,"text":"So by the '90s, believe it or not,"},{"time":199960,"text":"they were actually\nself-sufficient in food,"},{"time":203400,"text":"but they did it at a great cost."},{"time":205000,"text":"They did it at a cost of their aquifers,"},{"time":206960,"text":"they did it at a cost\nof their surface water."},{"time":209120,"text":"And of course, there are\nmany nonclimate issues"},{"time":211360,"text":"that also contributed to Syria."},{"time":213080,"text":"There was the Iraq War,"},{"time":214320,"text":"and as you can see\nby that lower blue line there,"},{"time":216760,"text":"over a million refugees\ncome into the cities."},{"time":220000,"text":"And then about a decade ago,"},{"time":221760,"text":"there's this tremendous\nheat wave and drought --"},{"time":224920,"text":"fingerprints all over that show,"},{"time":227000,"text":"yes, this is in fact related\nto the changing climate --"},{"time":230240,"text":"has put another three quarters\nof a million farmers"},{"time":233200,"text":"into those same cities."},{"time":235120,"text":"Why? Because they had nothing."},{"time":238200,"text":"They had dust. They had dirt.\nThey had nothing."},{"time":241200,"text":"So now they're in the cities,"},{"time":243240,"text":"the Iraqis are in the cities,"},{"time":244680,"text":"it's Assad, it's not like\nhe's taking care of his people,"},{"time":247800,"text":"and all of a sudden\nwe have just this huge issue here"},{"time":252120,"text":"of massive instability"},{"time":254400,"text":"and a breeding ground for extremism."},{"time":256680,"text":"And this is why in the security community"},{"time":258680,"text":"we call climate change\na risk to instability."},{"time":262400,"text":"It accelerates instability here."},{"time":264680,"text":"In plain English,\nit makes bad places worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268240,"text":"So let's go to another place here."},{"time":269920,"text":"Now we're going to go 2,000 kilometers,\nor about 1,200 miles, north of Oslo,"},{"time":274520,"text":"only 600 miles from the Pole,"},{"time":277080,"text":"and this is arguably"},{"time":279640,"text":"the most strategic island\nyou've never heard of."},{"time":281920,"text":"It's a place called Svalbard."},{"time":283520,"text":"It sits astride the sea lanes"},{"time":285760,"text":"that the Russian Northern Fleet needs\nto get out and go into warmer waters."},{"time":291040,"text":"It is also, by virtue of its geography,"},{"time":294040,"text":"a place where you can control\nevery single polar orbiting satellite"},{"time":297600,"text":"on every orbit."},{"time":298880,"text":"It is the strategic high ground of space."},{"time":301520,"text":"Climate change has greatly reduced\nthe sea ice around here,"},{"time":304800,"text":"greatly increasing human activity,"},{"time":307640,"text":"and it's becoming a flashpoint,"},{"time":309160,"text":"and in fact the NATO\nParliamentary Assembly"},{"time":311240,"text":"is going to meet here\non Svalbard next month."},{"time":314280,"text":"The Russians are very,\nvery unhappy about that."},{"time":317040,"text":"So if you want to find\na flashpoint in the Arctic,"},{"time":319720,"text":"look at Svalbard there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322440,"text":"Now, in the military,"},{"time":324240,"text":"we have known for decades,\nif not centuries,"},{"time":326600,"text":"that the time to prepare,"},{"time":328640,"text":"whether it's for a hurricane,\na typhoon or strategic changes,"},{"time":332400,"text":"is before they hit you,"},{"time":334280,"text":"and Admiral Nimitz was right there."},{"time":336000,"text":"That is the time to prepare."},{"time":338000,"text":"Fortunately, our Secretary of Defense,"},{"time":340520,"text":"Secretary Mattis,\nhe understands that as well,"},{"time":343600,"text":"and what he understands\nis that climate is a risk."},{"time":346680,"text":"He has said so in his written\nresponses to Congress,"},{"time":349160,"text":"and he says, \"As Secretary of Defense,"},{"time":351320,"text":"it's my job to manage such risks.\""},{"time":354760,"text":"It's not only the US military\nthat understands this."},{"time":358720,"text":"Many of our friends and allies\nin other navies and other militaries"},{"time":362280,"text":"have very clear-eyed views\nabout the climate risk."},{"time":366080,"text":"And in fact, in 2014, I was honored\nto speak for a half-a-day seminar"},{"time":370400,"text":"at the International Seapower Symposium"},{"time":372640,"text":"to 70 heads of navies about this issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377200,"text":"So Winston Churchill\nis alleged to have said,"},{"time":379800,"text":"I'm not sure if he said anything,\nbut he's alleged to have said"},{"time":383080,"text":"that Americans can always\nbe counted upon to do the right thing"},{"time":387040,"text":"after exhausting every other possibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":390720,"text":"So I would argue\nwe're still in the process"},{"time":392960,"text":"of exhausting every other possibility,"},{"time":394840,"text":"but I do think we will prevail."},{"time":397440,"text":"But I need your help."},{"time":398920,"text":"This is my ask."},{"time":400200,"text":"I ask not that you take\nyour recycling out on Wednesday,"},{"time":403680,"text":"but that you engage\nwith every business leader,"},{"time":406680,"text":"every technology leader,\nevery government leader,"},{"time":409520,"text":"and ask them, \"Ma'am, sir,"},{"time":412120,"text":"what are you doing\nto stabilize the climate?\""},{"time":415520,"text":"It's just that simple."},{"time":417080,"text":"Because when enough people care enough,"},{"time":420600,"text":"the politicians, most of whom\nwon't lead on this issue --"},{"time":424200,"text":"but they will be led --"},{"time":426000,"text":"that will change this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427400,"text":"Because I can tell you,\nthe ice doesn't care."},{"time":431480,"text":"The ice doesn't care\nwho's in the White House."},{"time":433920,"text":"It doesn't care which party\ncontrols your congress."},{"time":436920,"text":"It doesn't care which party\ncontrols your parliament."},{"time":439520,"text":"It just melts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442240,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}